      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="view-and-create-new-filters" data-step-uuid="21b5a61b-0cf1-414e-8e43-499536bf6a0d">
    <h2 id="view-and-create-new-filters" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Manage Gradebook Filters</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/007/722/945/original/ec2ed3ff-165c-47f0-9af5-b2dae0c200dc.png" srcset="" alt="Manage Gradebook Filters" height="715" width="484">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_50af2705-057f-4ce8-a37b-4eb2b3b9b2ed" class="text-block-content">
    <p>In the Saved Filters Preset sidebar, existing filters display. </p>
<p>To rename a filter, enter a new name in the <strong>Filter preset name</strong> field [1]. </p>
<p>To manage a filter preset's filter type, click a <strong>Filter Type</strong> drop-down menu [2].</p>
<p>To delete the filter, click the <strong>Delete</strong> <strong>Preset</strong> button [3]. </p>
<p>To create a new filter, click the <strong>Create Filter Preset </strong>expand arrow icon [4].</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="view-applied-filters" data-step-uuid="eacbf019-8525-4326-857b-258d63e0c274">
    <h2 id="view-applied-filters" class="step-title screensteps-heading">View Applied Filters</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <a href="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/008/184/325/original/a4e4fd6b-cf9d-4d07-9d99-12c1111c0a1e.png" class="screensteps-image-zoom" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">
